column5: I'll be there with three of my buddies OCT. 13th-18th. we'll be trolling cranks out of a maroon and white 1895 yar-craft storm with yamaha motors. when you goin? Maybe we'll have to get a beer. Gary
From the looks of it it should be a pretty good weekend with very little boat trafic. Gary
we will be up there the 12-18th, looking very much forward to it. It is only a month and a half away
what kind of boat you going to be fishing out of. Gary

Dang, I should have double checked this, think I saw you guys in the Skeeter on the 13th, we were in a red 1950 Tyee with a 175 Verado, had a decent day, 9 eyes, largest 10lb 10oz 30.5". But I don't recall seeing a YarCraft yesterday.....did you make it out on the 13th to fish or was that your travel day?
